The paper deals with the joint dynamics of information diffusion and network evolution in online social networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves the use of point process models, which suggests the sub-categories cs.SD (Systems and Control), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the co-evolutionary dynamics of the two processes, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks).
